@database HStringClass
@index "Classes.guide/Main"

@Node Main "RxMUI - HString Class"


HString class    @{"Index" link "Classes.guide/Main"} @{"Super" link "StringClass.guide/Main"}
@{u}                                                             @{uu}

  The HString class is used to create string gadgets with
  hystory.

  String is a subclass of String class, which is subclass of
  TextInput.mcc, so you must have TextInput.mcc in MUI:Libs/MUI
  to use it. TextInput.mcc is copyright of Oliver Wagner.

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Attributes@{ub}

  @{fg shine}HSFlash@{fg text}
  B I
  Flash the screen when got history bounds. Default 0.

  @{fg shine}HSMax@{fg text}
  N I
  Max entries in history. Min value is 2. Default unlimited.

  @{fg shine}HSNTClear@{fg text}
  B I
  If 1, the contents is not cleared when the user presses return;
  If 0, the contents is cleared any time the iser presses return.
  Default 0.

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Methods@{ub}

  @{fg shine}HSClearHistory@{fg text}
  -
  Clear history.

  @{u}                                                        @{uu}

 @{b}Note@{ub}

     1. Frame is forced to String, unless it is inited as None

     2. RemainActive is forced to 1, unless it is inited as 0

     3. Usually, AlwaysNotifyNC should be set to 1

@EndNode
